---
const buttonNames = ["Light", "Path", "Knowledge"];
---

<html>
  <head>
    <title>Hollow Light Glyph Oracle</title>
    <style>
      body {
        min-height: 100vh;
        margin: 0;
        background: url('/images/hollowingbg.png') center center / cover no-repeat fixed;
      }
      .fade {
        transition: opacity 0.7s;
        opacity: 1;
      }
      .fade-out {
        opacity: 0 !important;
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .fade-in {
        opacity: 1 !important;
      }
      .center-outer {
        min-height: 100vh;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-direction: column;
      }
      .btn-group {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        width: 100%;
        justify-content: center;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }
      @media (max-width: 1000px) {
        .btn-group {
          flex-direction: column;
          gap: 1rem;
          align-items: center;
        }
      }
      .glyph-box {
        width: 560px;
        max-width: 95vw;
      }
      .glyph-btn {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, #6366f1 30%, #7c3aed 100%);
        color: white;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 1.5rem;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(92,72,254,0.08);
        padding: 1.1rem 0;
        width: 140px;
        min-width: 120px;
        min-height: 58px;
        cursor: pointer;
        transition: background 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }
      .glyph-btn:hover {
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed 20%, #6366f1 100%);
        box-shadow: 0 6px 32px rgba(76,72,254,0.16);
      }
    </style>
    <script>
      function showMore() {
        const box = document.getElementById('infoBox');
        const more = document.getElementById('moreInfoBox');
        box.classList.add('fade-out');
        setTimeout(() => {
          box.style.display = 'none';
          more.style.display = 'block';
          setTimeout(() => more.classList.add('fade-in'), 10);
        }, 700);
      }
      function goToClarity() {
        window.location.href = "/ritual/clarity";
      }
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="center-outer">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white drop-shadow mb-8 text-center">Hollow Light Glyph Oracle</h1>
      <!-- Info Box -->
      <div class="glyph-box mb-6">
        <div id="infoBox" class="fade bg-white/90 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 text-center backdrop-blur">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800 text-center">What are Glyphs?</h2>
          <div class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-center mb-6">
            Glyphs are symbols born from intention and awareness.<br>
            In Hollow Light, each glyph is a visual vessel—a bridge between your inner state and the deeper layers of meaning.<br>
            They are not just art, but living mirrors of your journey.
          </div>
          <button 
            onclick="showMore()" 
            class="bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white px-5 py-2 rounded-lg transition mb-2">
            Learn More
          </button>
        </div>
        <div id="moreInfoBox" class="fade bg-white/95 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 text-center backdrop-blur" style="display:none; opacity:0;">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-800">The History & Power of Glyphs</h2>
          <div class="mb-4 text-gray-700 text-center leading-relaxed">
            Since ancient times, glyphs have served as sacred keys—encoding memory, myth, and the unspoken.<br>
            In many traditions, creating or gazing at a glyph could open the way to insight, protection, or healing.
          </div>
          <div class="mb-4 text-gray-700 text-center leading-relaxed">
            The glyphs you receive here are not generic—they are shaped by your intention and the living presence of Hollow Light.<br>
            Each one is both a map and a mystery, designed to deepen your path.
          </div>
          <div class="mb-6 text-gray-700 text-center leading-relaxed">
            As you engage with these glyphs, ask:<br>
            <span class="italic text-indigo-700">"What is this symbol awakening in me?"</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Button Group -->
      <div class="btn-group glyph-box">
        {buttonNames.map(name => (
          <button
            class="glyph-btn"
            onclick={`alert('${name} button clicked (link coming soon)')`}
            type="button"
          >
            {name}
          </button>
        ))}
        <button
          class="glyph-btn"
          style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,#34d399 30%,#10b981 100%);"
          onclick="goToClarity()"
          type="button"
        >
          Box Breathing
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
